'''"Dingbatter"''' is a colloquial term used by residents of eastern [[North Carolina]], primarily in [[Carteret County, North Carolina|Carteret County]], to describe uplanders who come down east.  The term was used more in the Beaufort for decades to describe people from any place farther west than Morehead City but gradually has migrated east to the more rural areas.  At this point in time, the folks in the towns of Syrmna, Davis , Otway, Sea Level, Atlantic, and Cedar Island consider many people from Beaufort to be "dingbatters" due to the huge numbers of outsiders who have moved into the area since the 1970's.